<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1557,1872]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
Type data: It is not clear from the original description how many specimens were used to describe this bee. In 1901, Friese considered a male studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Perty, J. A. M." box="[561,702,1593,1620]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="125 - 224" refId="ref10773" refString="Perty, J. A. M. (1833) Delectus animalium articulatorum, quae in itinere per Brasiliam annis MDCCCXVII-MDCCCXX jussu et auspiciis Maxilimiliani Josephi I. Bavariae regis augustissimi peracto collegerunt Dr. J. B. de Spix et Dr. C. F. Ph. de Martius. Fasc. 3. Author's edition, Munchen, 100 pp., pls. 25 - 40. [pp. 125 - 224] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 102991" type="book chapter" year="1833">Perty (1833)</bibRefCitation>
housed at 
<collectionCode box="[823,881,1593,1619]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4b7r-7sec" name="Bavarian State Collection of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="Museum">ZSM</collectionCode>
as the “type” of this species and according to the Article 74.6 of the 
<collectionCode box="[367,432,1629,1655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">ICZN</collectionCode>
code, this interpretation can be considered a valid 
<typeStatus box="[1010,1113,1629,1655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[1265,1436,1629,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref10360" refString="Moure, J. S. (1960 b) Notas sobre os tipos de abelhas do Brasil descritas por Perty em 1833 (Hymenoptera-Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade Federal do Parana, Zoologia, 1, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
did something similar, citing that he studied the “ 
<typeStatus box="[698,801,1665,1691]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
” of this species, assuming that it was described based on a single male exemplar. The specimen studied by these authors has the following data label: [green label] Piauchy. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,1737,1763]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
Coll. Perty [handwritten]\ [square label with green margin] 5. Bres. Piauchy 
<taxonomicName authority="Pty" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1125,1355,1737,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis box="[1125,1142,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1157,1311,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">xanthocnemis</emphasis>
Pty
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]\ [pink label] 
<typeStatus box="[387,511,1774,1800]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[518,848,1773,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis box="[518,783,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Xylocopa xanthocnemis</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[853,874,1774,1800]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
Diller 1989 [handwritten] Zoologische Staatssam- mlg. München [printed] (
<collectionCode box="[435,498,1809,1835]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4b7r-7sec" name="Bavarian State Collection of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="Museum">ZSM</collectionCode>
). Subsequent designation: 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[797,950,1809,1835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" pagination="237 - 350" refId="ref9913" refString="Friese, H. (1901 [1900]) Monographie der Bienengattung Centris (s. lat). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, Wien, 15, 237 - 350." type="journal article" year="1901">Friese (1901)</bibRefCitation>
